shearing gang
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a team of shearers and shed hands, often with a classer and cook.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka sheep-shearing gang, contract shearing gang
